FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

FeedPackage.Description:
With this client library you can easily add electronic signatures to your systems and exisitng work-flows based on the Underskrift API.
You can add electronic signatures to web forms, documents or other data regardless of file type. If you have security classed documents or if all parties have access to the documents you don't need to send the documents to us, you just have to send the documents SHA2-512 hash.
A case can be signed by one or multiple parties. Information about the parties can either be specified upfront or collected when signing. You choose if you want to communicate with the parites or if you want to use alread made templates.
Depending on the scenario different types of identification can be used, currently electronic-id, SMS and touch signatures are supported.

FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

FeedPackage.Description: A module for people who want to keep track of Item and Template changes while working on new features. It enables you to automatically track those changes and add additional Items manually to the process. At the end of your work, you can generate an Item Package which contains all those changes without having to go into the Package Designer and remember which Items you touched. All of this without leaving the Content Editor!

FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.
FeedPackage.Tags: Signere Sign BankID Digital signatur Uni Pluss Signere.no
FeedPackage.Title: Unipluss.Sign.ClientNET35
